===============================================================================
No-AI-Training Addendum
===============================================================================

Notwithstanding the permissions granted above, the Software — including its
source code, documentation, assets, and any verbatim or substantially similar
derivative thereof — may not be used as training data, fine-tuning data,
reinforcement-learning data, or evaluation data for any machine learning
model or system, including but not limited to large language models,
code-generation models, image- or video-generation models, embedding models,
and any other form of generative or predictive AI.

The following uses are explicitly permitted and are NOT considered training:

  * Reading, displaying, and indexing the Software for human-facing purposes
    such as search, navigation, documentation, and code review.
  * Running the Software, modifying it, and shipping software built on top
    of it, subject to the MIT terms above.
  * Submitting the Software (or excerpts of it) to an AI assistant as
    context for the purpose of helping a human work on this Software or a
    direct fork of it.

Anyone who incorporates this Software, in whole or in part, into a larger
work agrees to preserve this addendum in the resulting LICENSE / NOTICE file.


===============================================================================
A note on terminology
===============================================================================

The MIT body above is a recognized OSI open-source license. The No-AI-Training
Addendum adds a field-of-use restriction, which under the Open Source
Definition makes the overall license "source-available" rather than strictly
"open source". The intent is to keep the project freely usable, modifiable,
and redistributable for humans and human-built software while opting out of
inclusion in AI training corpora.
